AssetCacheLocatorService(8) System Manager's Manual AssetCacheLocatorService(8)

NAME

AssetCacheLocatorService — Service to find local macOS Content Caches

SYNOPSIS

AssetCacheLocatorService

DESCRIPTION

AssetCacheLocatorService finds macOS Content Caches on the local network.

There are no configuration options to AssetCacheLocatorService. Users should not run AssetCacheLocatorService manually.

DIAGNOSTICS

AssetCacheLocatorService logs to the os_log(3) subsystem com.apple.AssetCacheServices category Daemon.

SEE ALSO

System Settings > Sharing > Content Caching, log(1), AssetCache(8), AssetCacheLocatorUtil(8), AssetCacheManagerUtil(8)
